# 2003-09-16.bmh.1.mgs: Partnering with Transforming Knowledge Spaces

September 16th, 2003

This resolution was adopted by the Board of Directors of SPI at their
meeting of [October 14, 2003](/meetings/minutes/2003/2003-10-14).

### WHEREAS,

1. The "Transforming Knowledge Spaces: Open Technologies for
   Research Collaboration and Research Communication" project
   (henceforth referred to as "the project") at the Intellectual
   Property Research Institute of Australia is seeking international
   partners to advise and participate in the project.

2. The project will include the development of Free Software as a
   central part of research.

3. Partnership of SPI for this project allows an explicit avenue
   for involvement of its members and also allows for the involvement
   of SPI as an organization without commitment from members or from
   the organization.

### IT IS HEREBY RESOLVED THAT,

1. Software in the Public Interest, Inc. will join the project in
   an advisory and participatory role as an international
   partner.

2. Benjamin 'Mako' Hill will act as advisor to the project and gather
   input from SPI, its members, projects and their members.

